# CSS/SCSS Styling Guidelines

This site uses Bulma CSS framework with custom SCSS overrides.

## Architecture
- **Base framework**: Bulma CSS ([css/bulma.min.css](mdc:css/bulma.min.css))
- **Custom styles**: [css/index.scss](mdc:css/index.scss) - Main stylesheet that imports base styles
- **SCSS partials**: [_sass/_base.scss](mdc:_sass/_base.scss) - Contains base font family definition

## Key CSS Classes
- `.publication-block` - Container for publication entries
- `.publication-title` - Publication titles (110% font size, weight 600)
- `.publication-authors` - Author listings with special `.author-me` highlighting
- `.publication-venue` - Conference/journal venue styling
- `.publication-description` - Description text
- `.publication-links` - Button containers for links
- `.portrait` - Profile image container with 2% border radius and transform scale
- `.navbar-burger` - Mobile navigation hamburger menu

## Typography
- **Primary font**: "Noto Sans", sans-serif (defined in [_sass/_base.scss](mdc:_sass/_base.scss))
- **Title font**: 'Google Sans', weight 700 for `.title` class
- **Academic icons**: Academicons and Font Awesome integration

## Responsive Design
- Mobile-first approach with Bulma's responsive utilities
- Navbar transforms to burger menu on mobile
- Portrait image adjustments for smaller screens
- Uses `@media screen and (max-width: 750px)` for mobile breakpoints

## Color Scheme
- Primary text: #000 (black)
- Venue text: #555 (gray)
- Awards: firebrick color
- Light theme with subtle contrasts

## Custom Features
- Mouseover effects for publication images/videos
- External link styling with icons
- Disabled link styles for items without URLs
- Fixed navbar with proper spacing compensation
